formatted_address: 5A, Jalan Eko Botani 3/5, Taman, Persiaran Eko Botani, 79100 Iskandar Puteri, Johor Darul Ta'zim, Malaysia
name: GO HOW Cafe

reviews.text:
Lemon tea is very thick infused w lemongrass, superb.

Kimchi fried rice is the best one I have ever had - flavourful and moist!

Chicken big serving and yum, mapo tofu v flavourful too.

A rare clean and pleasant environment, hidden gem indeed!

My first visit.  A warm welcome by Mr Ho.  Handsome oppa
Clean cafe, cosy
Tasty food.  We had chicken mayo rice, ramen, fresh salad.  Choc drink premium, my daughter loves it.  Husband like the matcha latte!  Will visit again

When I visited here, I was so moved by the peaceful interior. The coffee was so fresh and you can taste the best coffee by far. It is run by a Korean family, so you can taste delicious Korean food. If you come to Eco Botanic, I recommend you to visit
Go How Cafe has a cosy welcoming vibe run buy a young korean family. I tried their Kimchi Fried Rice and Toppoki and it taste superb. If you are in Eco Botanic, must give this place a try.

The food here is so good! The first time we came, we had the kimchi fried rice and tteokbokki, and they were amazing. We’ve been coming back ever since. The salted egg spaghetti is really good too, and the portions are big. Recently, we tried the matcha latte from the new menu, and it’s honestly the best I’ve ever had. The service is great, and the food always comes out fast. Definitely a favourite spot!

vicinity: 5A, Jalan Eko Botani 3/5, Taman, Persiaran Eko Botani, Iskandar Puteri
